A minibus accident has left five people dead. According to police reports the accident happened on the  N5 near Bethlehem after a minibus taxi overturned. News24 reports that the vehicle was carrying teachers and school governing body members from Sekoko Primary school in Paul Roux. The passengers were heading home from a workshop in Tweeling when the accident occurred. Police spokesperson Captain Phumelelo Dhlamini shared in a statement that the driver lost control of the vehicle. "Four women and a man were declared dead on the scene. Seven passengers sustained severe injuries. They were rushed to Dihlabeng Regional Hospital, Phekolong Hospital, and Medi-Clinic Hospital. A case of culpable homicide is being investigated to determine the cause of the accident," Dhlamini added  